Application Help
How to use the application?
Enter the coordinates of points A, B, C, D, and P using the NumericUpDown fields.
You can move the points by clicking and dragging with the mouse.
Coordinates are restricted to the range 0 - 450 to ensure the points remain within the drawing area.
How to determine the position of point P?
Point P is evaluated in relation to the quadrilateral:
Green - The point is inside.
Orange - The point is on the edge.
Blue - The point is on the vertex.
Red - The point is outside the quadrilateral.
What if I cannot enter certain values?
The application prevents line intersections and incorrect point ordering.
If you enter an invalid value, a warning will appear, and the value will revert to the last valid position.
